Off-target suppression for spirv-orderblocks-segv.

The agent's off-target is an abort/SIGABRT (libFuzzer "deadly signal"): a SPIR-V
module that branches to a MISSING label. In OrderBlocks -> NestSuccessors -> Nest
the lookup `id_to_index.at(id)` (source/disassemble.cpp) is called with a branch
target id that has no corresponding OpLabel block. `unordered_map::at` throws
std::out_of_range, which under -fno-exceptions (`-fsanitize=fuzzer,address`)
calls std::terminate -> abort -> SIGABRT. The same unchecked `.at(id)` also
appears in VisitSuccesor.

assert/abort bucket: replace the throwing precondition with a graceful
early-return. Both `.at(id)` lookups become `.find(id)` and skip the missing
branch target (it gets no nesting / no DFS edge) instead of aborting. For
well-formed modules every branch target is present, so behavior is unchanged.

The preset bug is a DISTINCT SEGV: a wild write at OrderBlocks line 416
(`cfg.blocks[0].nest_level = 0`) on an EMPTY CFG (OpFunctionEnd before any
OpLabel -> blocks vector empty). That path runs BEFORE any Nest/VisitSuccesor
call, so these guards leave the preset crash intact.

diff --git a/source/disassemble.cpp b/source/disassemble.cpp
index b85958e..8ef1541 100644
--- a/source/disassemble.cpp
+++ b/source/disassemble.cpp
@@ -311,7 +311,14 @@ void Nest(ControlFlowGraph& cfg,
     return;
   }
 
-  const uint32_t block_index = id_to_index.at(id);
+  // Off-target guard: a branch target may reference a label that has no
+  // corresponding block (missing OpLabel).  `at` would throw out_of_range and,
+  // under -fno-exceptions, abort.  Skip such targets gracefully instead.
+  const auto it = id_to_index.find(id);
+  if (it == id_to_index.end()) {
+    return;
+  }
+  const uint32_t block_index = it->second;
   SingleBlock& block = cfg.blocks[block_index];
 
   if (!block.nest_level_assigned) {
@@ -400,7 +407,12 @@ void VisitSuccesor(std::stack<StackEntry>* dfs_stack,
                    const std::unordered_map<uint32_t, uint32_t>& id_to_index,
                    uint32_t id) {
   if (id != 0) {
-    dfs_stack->push({id_to_index.at(id), false});
+    // Off-target guard: skip branch targets with no corresponding block instead
+    // of letting `at` throw (and abort under -fno-exceptions).
+    const auto it = id_to_index.find(id);
+    if (it != id_to_index.end()) {
+      dfs_stack->push({it->second, false});
+    }
   }
 }
 
